Below is a worked‐through example of how one can interpret and build the two structures shown in the main image.  I have broken it into three parts:

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) DETAILED DESCRIPTION OF THE MAIN TARGET IMAGE
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

■ OVERALL LAYOUT
The scene actually contains two separate “builds.”  
• On the LEFT is a tall, open‐frame tower made mostly of green and yellow rectangular blocks, with an orange cylinder for support and a small blue cube on top.  
• On the RIGHT is a triangular “house‐shaped” structure that has a red arch (with a circular opening) in the middle of its base and several orange triangular wedges forming sloping sides and a roof.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A) LEFT‐HAND STRUCTURE
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Count & Layers
• It uses NINE pieces stacked from bottom to top.  
• From the ground up: a green rectangular block forms the base, an orange cylinder sits on it, then a horizontal yellow bar, two vertical green bars on either side, another yellow bar above them, a small orange triangular wedge nestled in the middle, another green bar on top, and finally a small blue cube at the very top.

Spatial Relationships (bottom‐to‐top)
1) A flat green rectangular block on the floor.  
2) An orange cylinder stands vertically centered on that green block.  
3) A yellow rectangular block spans horizontally above the cylinder.  
4) Two tall green rectangular blocks stand vertically on the left and right ends of that yellow block (making a “door‐frame”).  
5) Another yellow rectangular piece sits horizontally on top of those two green columns.  
6) An orange triangular wedge is placed inside that frame (pointing upward).  
7) Above the frame is another green rectangular block spanning horizontally.  
8) Finally, one small blue cube rests on top.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
B) RIGHT‐HAND STRUCTURE
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Count & Layers
• It uses NINE pieces arranged in three “rows.”  
• Bottom row has five blocks across (two orange wedges at the extreme left/right corners, two yellow squares just inside those wedges, and a red arch with a circular cutout in the very center).  
• Above that are two small cubes (green and blue).  
• Capping it all are two more orange wedges forming the triangular “roof.”

Spatial Relationships (bottom‐to‐top)
1) Bottom‐left corner: orange wedge.  
2) Next in from the left: a yellow cube.  
3) Center of the bottom row: red arch block (the circular hole is in this piece).  
4) Next in from the right: a second yellow cube.  
5) Bottom‐right corner: another orange wedge.  
6) Above the arch (second row): a green cube on the left, a blue cube on the right.  
7) Top row: two orange wedges meeting in the middle to form a high triangular peak.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2) SELECTING THE CORRECT BLOCKS FROM THE DICTIONARY
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Below is the dictionary index and how each piece is used.  Importantly, no rotation is allowed beyond what is shown in the dictionary image; the block must be used exactly in the orientation depicted.

LEFT STRUCTURE (9 blocks total):
1) Green rectangular block (horizontal) at bottom → Index 8  
2) Orange cylinder → Index 12  
3) Yellow rectangular block (first horizontal “frame” piece) → Index 10  
4) Green rectangular block (vertical, left column) → Index 9  
5) Green rectangular block (vertical, right column) → Index 9 again  
6) Yellow rectangular block (second horizontal “frame” piece) → Index 10 again  
7) Orange triangular wedge inside the frame → Index 15  
8) Green rectangular block (horizontal, very top) → Index 8 again  
9) Blue cube (on top) → Index 3  

RIGHT STRUCTURE (9 blocks total):
1) Bottom‐left orange wedge → Index 13  
2) Bottom‐left yellow cube → Index 5  
3) Red arch (center with circular opening) → Index 1  
4) Bottom‐right yellow cube → Index 5 again  
5) Bottom‐right orange wedge → Index 13 again  
6) Green cube (middle row, left) → Index 4  
7) Blue cube (middle row, right) → Index 6  
8) Top‐left orange wedge → Index 14  
9) Top‐right orange wedge → Index 16  

So in total, you will be reusing indices 5, 8, 9, 10, 13 where needed, since multiple copies of the same dictionary shape exist in the final build.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3) STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY INFERENCES
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Below is one logical order (bottom to top, left structure first, then right structure).  Follow the exact template:

{
   Step1: Move block with index 8    // Bottom green base (left structure)
   Step2: Move block with index 12   // Orange cylinder on top
   Step3: Move block with index 10   // Yellow bar (lower “frame” piece)
   Step4: Move block with index 9    // Green vertical column (left side)
   Step5: Move block with index 9    // Green vertical column (right side)
   Step6: Move block with index 10   // Yellow bar (upper “frame” piece)
   Step7: Move block with index 15   // Orange triangular wedge in frame
   Step8: Move block with index 8    // Green bar across the top
   Step9: Move block with index 3    // Blue cube at the very top

   Step10: Move block with index 13  // Bottom-left orange wedge (right structure)
   Step11: Move block with index 5   // Bottom-left yellow cube
   Step12: Move block with index 1   // Red arch in center
   Step13: Move block with index 5   // Bottom-right yellow cube
   Step14: Move block with index 13  // Bottom-right orange wedge
   Step15: Move block with index 4   // Middle-row green cube
   Step16: Move block with index 6   // Middle-row blue cube
   Step17: Move block with index 14  // Top-left orange wedge (roof)
   Step18: Move block with index 16  // Top-right orange wedge (roof)
}

That completes the two assembled shapes exactly as shown in the main image, using the listed dictionary blocks without further rotation.
